{"hash":"9fdb27b34121f3ba7283cb1e0e0da68a9bcb720e","data":{"subject":{"title":"CSS3/HTML5","belongsTo":{"edges":[{"node":{"title":"Hosting the HTML5 front-end Test UI on your site – Ookla Speedtest Custom","path":"/content/work/hosting-the-htm-l5-front-end-test-ui-on-your-site-o/","date":"December 2017","timeToRead":1,"description":"Since many of Ookla's customers were new to the concept of using a iframe hosted from another web server, we needed to build a template to assist users with building their company web pages that displayed the test content in an HTML5 friendly manner.","content":"\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/hosting.png","company":"Ookla (Speedtest.net)","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Updating your NetGauge site to host the STC test – Ookla Speedtest Custom","path":"/content/work/updating-your-net-gauge-site-to-host-the-stc-test-o/","date":"December 2017","timeToRead":1,"description":"The client-side technology used to execute and host a test on a customer's website was completely rehauled and required a different approach to get similar results on the client's site. We worked to make this process as simple as possible for users who were used to a more complicated approach to hosting the test engine.","content":"\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/updating.png","company":"Ookla (Speedtest.net)","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"}]}},{"node":{"title":"How Do I Upgrade to Speedtest Custom from NetGauge? – Ookla Speedtest Custom","path":"/content/work/how-do-i-upgrade-to-speedtest-custom-from-net-gauge/","date":"December 2017","timeToRead":1,"description":"Many of Ookla's licensed vendors were using the legacy Flash technology that was quickly becoming discontinued and blocked by security enhancements to major browsers. Our major effort involved helping ISPs and other networking vendors understand the new technology involved and provided high-level tutorials to help ensure that their plan to update their website would go as smoothly as possible.","content":"\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/howdoi.png","company":"Ookla (Speedtest.net)","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"},{"id":"Browser Networking","path":"/subject/browser-networking/","title":"Browser Networking"},{"id":"JavaScript","path":"/subject/java-script/","title":"JavaScript"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Passing Test Results To The Browser – Ookla Speedtest Custom","path":"/content/work/passing-test-results-to-the-browser-ookla-speedtes/","date":"December 2017","timeToRead":1,"description":"Ookla's Speedtest Custom provided automatic storage of test results hosted in the online reporting dashboard for each license, however sometimes users needed to capture more information than we provided by the licensed features. To help with customer use cases, the JavaScript client leveraged the browser's Window.postMessage() method to enable safe cross-origin communication between the client's test instance and their self-hosted desired database.","content":"\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/passing.png","company":"Ookla (Speedtest.net)","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"},{"id":"JavaScript","path":"/subject/java-script/","title":"JavaScript"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Burger Time! (CSS Only)","path":"/content/work/burger-time-css-only/","date":"January 2017","timeToRead":1,"description":"Not sure why this is the first thing I thought of when I saw a daily CSS challenge on the topic of \"hamburgers\", but building this demo using only CSS compontents brought back a lot of fond memories!","content":"<iframe height=\"775\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"Burger Time! (CSS Only)\" src=\"https://codepen.io/watthem/embed/qRjwPq?height=775&theme-id=dark&default-tab=result\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href='https://codepen.io/watthem/pen/qRjwPq'>Burger Time! (CSS Only)</a> by Matthew Hendricks\n  (<a href='https://codepen.io/watthem'>@watthem</a>) on <a href='https://codepen.io'>CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/burger.png","company":"Codpen.io","tags":[{"id":"Front-end development","path":"/tag/front-end-development/","title":"Front-end development"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Arthur's Nightlight","path":"/content/work/arthur-s-night-light/","date":"November 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"A robot designed with CSS only that illuminates the page when powered on.","content":"<iframe height=\"265\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"Arthur's Nightlight\" src=\"https://codepen.io/watthem/embed/RoZjPy?height=265&theme-id=dark&default-tab=result\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href='https://codepen.io/watthem/pen/RoZjPy'>Arthur's Nightlight</a> by Matthew Hendricks\n  (<a href='https://codepen.io/watthem'>@watthem</a>) on <a href='https://codepen.io'>CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n<p><img src=\"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/robot.jpg\" alt=\"robot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/robot2.jpg\" alt=\"robot\"></p>\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/robot.png","company":"Codpen.io","tags":[{"id":"Front-end development","path":"/tag/front-end-development/","title":"Front-end development"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Canvas Dots on Mouse Events","path":"/content/work/canvas-dots-on-mouse-events/","date":"November 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"Just a simple demo using the browser Canvas API used to draw graphics on a web page via JavaScript. Dots are created and highlighted by interacting with mouse (or touch) events.","content":"<iframe height=\"265\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"Catch the dots\" src=\"https://codepen.io/watthem/embed/JbEYoz?height=265&theme-id=dark&default-tab=result\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href='https://codepen.io/watthem/pen/JbEYoz'>Catch the dots</a> by Matthew Hendricks\n  (<a href='https://codepen.io/watthem'>@watthem</a>) on <a href='https://codepen.io'>CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/canvas.png","company":"Codpen.io","tags":[{"id":"Front-end development","path":"/tag/front-end-development/","title":"Front-end development"}],"subjects":[{"id":"JavaScript","path":"/subject/java-script/","title":"JavaScript"},{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"},{"id":"DirectX","path":"/subject/direct-x/","title":"DirectX"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Google Inbox Sun and Clouds","path":"/content/work/google-inbox-sun-and-clouds/","date":"November 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"An animated version of the image used in Google's Inbox zero inbox layout.","content":"<iframe height=\"265\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"Google Inbox Sun and Clouds\" src=\"https://codepen.io/watthem/embed/xREydy?height=265&theme-id=dark&default-tab=result\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href='https://codepen.io/watthem/pen/xREydy'>Google Inbox Sun and Clouds</a> by Matthew Hendricks\n  (<a href='https://codepen.io/watthem'>@watthem</a>) on <a href='https://codepen.io'>CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/sun.png","company":"Codpen.io","tags":[{"id":"Front-end development","path":"/tag/front-end-development/","title":"Front-end development"}],"subjects":[{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Content Management - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/content-management-ninja-trader-8-help-guide/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"As a Product Manager for NinjaTrader, one of my core day to day responsibilities was maintaining the online help content aimed at an audience of both financial day traders and C# developers.","content":"\n","cover_image":"https://mscott.b-cdn.net/images/contentmgmt.png","company":"NinjaTrader LLC","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":".NET-C#","path":"/subject/net-c/","title":".NET-C#"},{"id":"CSS3/HTML5","path":"/subject/cs-s3-htm-l5/","title":"CSS3/HTML5"},{"id":"JavaScript","path":"/subject/java-script/","title":"JavaScript"},{"id":"Multi-threaded programming","path":"/subject/multi-threaded-programming/","title":"Multi-threaded programming"}]}}]}},"tags":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"Front-end development","title":"Front-end development","path":"/tag/front-end-development/"}},{"node":{"id":"Mindfulness & Mental Health","title":"Mindfulness & Mental Health","path":"/tag/mindfulness-and-mental-health/"}},{"node":{"id":"Product Management","title":"Product Management","path":"/tag/product-management/"}},{"node":{"id":"Project Management","title":"Project Management","path":"/tag/project-management/"}},{"node":{"id":"Technical writing","title":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/technical-writing/"}}]}},"context":{}}